<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> LOTR Q&A Rulings from 9/11/03<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.89)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617'>Enrique "Max of Tat" Huerta</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=617&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> September 25, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Originally posted on 9/11/03.<br />
Not for review.<br />
=============================<br />
<br />
Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   Good news all! My brother&#39;s back from Iraq!! He returned home to Twentynine Palms last Saturday. (= Much happiness...<br />
<br />
   DragonCon was a blast. If you&#39;ve never been to DragonCon, I HIGHLY recommend going. But remember to bring a camera with plenty of film, and an extra pillow if you&#39;re rooming with Hayes Hunter. (= Congratulations to Johnny Chu for winning the Star Wars:CCG World Championship. Also, congratulations to Michael Dalton from pulling off the improbably victory to win the Premier Series Event.<br />
<br />
   Next on my schedule is a bunch of local tournaments in Tucson and then it&#39;s off to Germany for Spiel! I look forward to meeting all of the internation people I don&#39;t usually get to meet. So if you&#39;re at Essen, please be sure to stop and say, &quot;Hi!&quot;. (=<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<br />
<b>this is probally a stupid question but here it is: <br />
some ents like ent horde say they cost -2 twilight for each ent or hobbit you can spot. im assuming you cant combine this to make it -2 for each unbound hobbit and ent right? [Demented Ent]</b><br />
<br />
There&#39;s rarely a stupid question you can ask me. Always feel free to ask, that&#39;s why I&#39;m here.<br />
<br />
For all of the Ents that have a twilight reduction based on the number of Ents and/or Hobbits you can spot here is how you calculate that reduction. Count up all of the Ents and unbound you can spot. Multiply that by the reduction factor and you&#39;ve got your total reduction. NOTE: Whether the gametext says &quot;and&quot; or &quot;or&quot;, you count up both Ents and unbound Hobbits and count them both.<br />
<br />
The Ent Hordes twilight cost would be -10 if you stop 3 Ents and 2 unbound Hobbits<br />
when you play it.<br />
<br />
<b>If you play Orc Purshuer, who makes each orcs site number -1, can you play three of him to make it -3 for the next orc or is it a cumulative rule. [Tyler] </b><br />
<br />
There is no cumulative rule in Lord of the Rings. In other words, everything is cumulative. So if you have 3 Orc Pursuers on the table, the site number for all [Sauron] Orcs would be -3.<br />
<br />
<b>2 questions: If &quot;no retreat&quot; is on a site, and I liberate that site, does that card die? Is it&#39;s affect (or, in this case, potentional affect) suspended until the site is recontrolled? I understand this is incredibly similar to an earlier question, but I want to make sure that your rule applies equally for site conditions. Next question: Eregion&#39;s trails, 1C 104, Maneuver: Exert a ranger to make each roaming minion strength -3 until the regroup phase. This has sparked a hot debate between my friends, with the ring-bound rangers and all. WHEN THE CARD IS PLAYED, the minions are not roaming (generally), however, when the skirmishes occur, and the strength counts, they are roaming. The card DOES SAY &quot;until the regroup phase&quot;, which is my argument. I find it to be no different than Faramir&#39;s cloak (roamers are strength -1) and Henneth Annun (roamers are strength -2 at site tower 6). They don&#39;t lose their strength until the skirmish, and if enough ancient roads and/or gondorian rangers are discarded/killed that the minions are not roaming, then the strength subtraction is, quite obviously, obliviated. Could you shed some light on this? Thanks a lot [Alex Maslow]</b><br />
<br />
1. When you liberate a site, all cards on that site are discarded. So if No Retreat is on the site, it would be placed in its owners discard pile. Controlling the site again, will not bring it back into play.<br />
<br />
2. You&#39;ll probably want to check out my answer to Koji from this week&#39;s update. The short answer is that NO Eregion Trails will not affect minions that are not roaming when it&#39;s played, but become roaming later.<br />
<br />
The reasoning is that when you play events you only affect cards that currently meet the requirements. If it was a condition or similar &quot;permanent&quot; card on the table, those effects would be continuously check and if a minion later became roaming they would be effected. Although the effects of an event may last for a while, its targets are only check the moment it&#39;s played.<br />
<br />
<b>hi, i&#39;ve read somewhere here on decktech in a report that you can make hrethel str +3 even if the minion doesn&#39;t have a wound? my question off course is : is this true :D [The Gaffer]</b><br />
<br />
Yes and no. Yes, you probably did read it here on DeckTech. I think I even know which report you read that in. But the answer is that NO you can not make Hrethel strength +3 is the minion he&#39;s skirmishing was not wounded when you heal it. Healing the minins is the cost of Hrethel&#39;s game text. If you don&#39;t pay the cost, you don&#39;t get the effect.<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<br />
<b>is a companion considered skirmishing when it is not his skirmish? for example, does ancient roads make minions not in the current skirmish roaming for arrows thick in the air? thanks, [KOJI]</b><br />
<br />
Koji writes so many times he already knows the format in which I put the questions in.  (= As usual, you bring up a good question.<br />
<br />
A character is considered &quot;skirmishing&quot; only if they are participating in the skirmish that is currently resolving. Any effect that mentions &quot;skirmishing&quot; will only work if it involves characters that are in the currently resolving skirmish.<br />
<br />
Ancient Roads only makes minions in the current skirmish site number +2. If the minions NOT in the currently resolving Skirmish are not roaming, they would be unaffected by Arrows Think in the Air.<br />
<br />
<b>Hi, I&#39;m new to the game and I&#39;ve a silly cuestion ... the rules says that the FP players assign minions to his companions on a 1 on 1 basis, and that the shadow player may assign any leftover minions. My cuestion is: those extra minions are also assigned using the &quot;1 on1&quot; criterium? example: shadow player with 6 minions, FP player with 3 companions. The extra 3 minions can be assigned to Frodo or do I have to end assigning 2 per companion? Thanks! [Pablo]</b><br />
<br />
When the Shadow player assigns minions, they are allowed to assign them any way they wish. (So long as they only assign characters that are allowed to participate in the skirmishes.)<br />
<br />
So if there are 6 minions against 3 companions, the Shadow player would be allowed to assign the left over minions to any companions. (3 on one, 2 on one and 1 on another, 1 on each, or even not assign the extra ones at all.)<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
